{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "RiPPLE assigns each resource for evaluation to multiple reviewers (moderators), which then requires a consensus approach by optimally integrating the decisions made by multiple people towards an accurate final decision.",
    "In assessing the quality of student submissions based on scores from multiple assessors, we analyzed 18 inference models across five established categories of consensus approaches on data collected via RiPPLE (Darvishi et al., 2022a).",
    "The first utilized summary statistics like mean or median (e.g., Purchase & Hamer, 2018).",
    "The second leveraged historical performance or self-evaluation data to estimate student competence, a method often found in adaptive educational systems.",
    "The third applied probabilistic consensus techniques, assessing student reliability based on their previous reviews, a strategy effective in crowdsourcing systems (e.g., Raykar et al., 2010)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
